   "source": [
    "## Q6 – Job Offers\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of computing all the ways to get at least one offer, it’s much faster to compute the opposite case.\n",
    "\n",
    "P(no offers) = (0.8)^4.\n",
    "So P(at least one offer) = 1 − (0.8)^4 ≈ 0.59.\n",
    "\n",
    "This made it clear that the 90% claim is way too optimistic."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e777b4c3",
