   "source": [
    "## Q10 – Conditional Distribution\n",
    "\n",
    "For jointly normal variables, the conditional distribution is also normal.\n",
    "\n",
    "Here, X given Y = y has:\n",
    "- Mean = 1 + (y − 2)/3\n",
    "- Variance = 11/3."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5b92cb4f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Q11 – Linear Combination\n",
    "\n",
    "Since Z = 3X − 2Y is a linear combination of Gaussian variables, Z is Gaussian as well.\n",
    "\n",
    "The variance comes out to 13, and the correlation with X is 1/√13."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fc3b946d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Q12 – Conditional Mean and Variance\n",
    "\n",
    "Applying the standard multivariate normal formulas:\n",
    "\n",
    "E[X | Y = y, Z = z] = (11y + 5z) / 14\n",
    "Var(X | Y, Z) = 25 / 14."
   ]
